<headline>Special Weather Statement issued January 04 at 7:32AM MST  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...Widely scattered heavy snow showers will impact the morning
commute...
Heavy snow showers will continue to impact the area this morning,
leading to highly variable weather conditions at times.
While snow showers will only last for 15 to 30 minutes at a time,
these snow showers will result in rapid reductions in visibility
to 1/4 mile, along with a quick half inch to an inch of new snow.
If traveling this morning, give yourself extra time to reach your
destination, and use your headlights to make yourself more
visible to other motorists.</description>
